{
  "text": "Differential power analysis (DPA) is a type of attack that can reveal the secret key of a cryptographic device by statistically analyzing the correlation between the processed data and power traces [CITATION_1] . They are regarded as the most powerful of all side channel attacks on cryptographic devices because they can successfully extract secret keys even when measured power traces are very noisy.",
